

    
       "One of the things I don’t hear enough about from many usability professionals/pundits is the importance of specific interface elements setting expectations. “What happens next after when I click this button?” “Can I cancel this order later?” “What if I can’t do what this button is asking me to do?” “What do I need for step 3 of this four step process?” The answers to these little questions are absolutely critical when it comes to building a great customer experience online." 
    
    
